review_blob: Bottle says it was bottled in 2007 and I bought it in 2009.  Strong cherries scent with a bit of cherries in the taste as well.  The taste was very yeasty but that is to be expected from a quad.

beer_brewer_name: Coney Island Brewing Company (Boston Beer Company)
review_blob: Blood red with a slight fruity taste.  Rather sweet.  Very slight bitter finish but not too noticeable.
It poured with an excellent brown/dark tan color leaving a moderate off white head.  Great floral and citrus tastes.

This was a great beer, with a strong hops profile.  Definitely one of the better stouts with coffee/espresso.  It came on strong with the coffee and in the aftertaste there was a distinct hint of vanilla. It had an excellent color profile.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Espresso Oak Aged

review_blob: At 3.99 Lagunitas definitely offers a bargain for a bomber.  It doesnt come on very strong and it ends with a slight fruit taste.  It pours with minimum head and lacks carbonation.  Its good but it seems to lack something that would make it GREAT.  I would say that it falls in line with the rest of the line of Zappa beers.
beer_name: Lagunitas Cruising with Ruben and The Jets

review_blob: It had a good chocolate smell, with a strong smokey aftertaste.  The strong carbonation complimented the strong hops.

The taste was a deep roasted coffee with intense dark chocolate mixture.  The smell was definitely pretty roasty and smokey.  In my book its not as good as bells expedition or ten fidy but its a close 2nd/2.5 after ten fidy.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Overall I would have to say this was a great beer.  It had a nice mix of coffee and fruity flavors.

It has a nice dark copper color which was very pleasing to the eyes.  A consistent foam and carbonation left rings on the glass but not too much carbonation when tasted.  Tasted slightly of cherries and citrus.  The hops gave it a nice floral taste but not overpowering.

It had a pretty nice finish that left almost a fruity feeling.  It had a dark licorice taste at first but then a slight roasted profile.  The alcohol was well hidden behind the flavor.  I didnt notice the high alcohol content until I looked at the bottle.
The cherry flavor was pretty strong, and there was a hint of roast once you got past the cherry.  It was a bit too sweet for my tastes.

It pours dark with minimal head.  Definite roasted flavors with strong dark chocolate overtones.  Much more carbonation on the palate than the minimal head would give an indication of.  Slight pomegranate taste which is not easily noticeable over the chocolate and coffee overtones.  Its a delicious brew.

Has to be one of my favorite beers. Its seriously just phenomenal.  Well disguised alcohol and bitterness.  Pours as black as the darkest night, but has a taste much better than the night could ever have.  Out of the stouts that I have tasted this one, in my book, is right behind bells expedition stout.
This was a most delightful beer.  It had a flowery aroma with a taste to match.  Very drinkable even with such a high IBU.

I noticed a hint of pepper which gave it a sort of weird tacoey taste to me.  Not the full taco, just that extra liquid that drains from your soft shell when you eat it.  The aroma was definitely a delightful citrus scent.  The head was nice and full, almost reaching to rim of my glass.  Overall I would say that it is a most delightful beer, which would enhance any meal.
